            Research Notes

            • CFB - Boykin struggles against extra coverage

              Trevone Boykin struggled when Minnesota dropped eight or more defenders into coverage, completing 14.3% of his passes with an interception. When the Gophers did not, Boykin completed over 70% and threw his only touchdown pass of the game.

            • CFB-Boykin needs to improve the deep ball

              Trevone Boykin completed 2-of-12 passes on throws of 15 yards or farther downfield, seven of which were off-target. Boykin completed 34.2% of such passes last season, below the Power 5 average (38.0%) and 43rd out of 60 Power 5 quarterbacks with at least 50 such attempts.
